  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (v0.5 synthetic)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. The power-law hemolysis damage accumulation model (Giersiepen-Wurzinger formulation) is applied under the theoretical precondition that red blood cell damage accumulates linearly along streamlines — an assumption broadly applicable to laminar and mildly turbulent flows. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2).",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/cpb-hemolysis-mrl2",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/cpb-hemolysis-worst-case-identification",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/cfd-giersiepen-wurzinger-hemolysis",
